# Enterprise WhatsApp Buyer UX

## Architecture (single sources of truth)

| Concern | Module | Rule |
|---------|--------|------|
| CRM button flags | `buyerEnterpriseUx.service.ts` → `buildBuyerCrmButtonFlags` | Never duplicate visit/project id logic in orchestrators |
| Visit-era buttons | `buildActiveVisitActionButtons` + `shouldUseVisitAwareButtonsOnly` | Active visit → no Book Visit / Property Details except visit-scheduling prompts |
| Buyer copy | `buyerI18n.util.ts` → `tBuyer()` | No `buyerTurn("literal")` in interactive orchestrator — enforced by `buyerCopyCompliance.test.ts` |
| Sold units | `resolveBuyerPropertyReferenceEnterprise` + `propertyBrowseTurn` | Sold by name → explanation + View Listings, never silent empty |
| Language | `resolveTurnBuyerLanguage` / `resolveInteractiveBuyerLanguage` | Message language wins; Hi → English + Hindi suffix if `leadLanguage=hi` |
| Browse filters | `buildDiscoveryButtonSet(snapshot, lang)` | Always pass `lang` — never cache localized titles in Redis snapshot |

## Invariants (must never break)

1. **Booked property tap** → `visit_booked_property_reminder`, not full detail repeat.
2. **Active visit + any AI reply** → Change Time / View Listings / Call Agent (catch-all in `resolveSituationBuyerButtons`).
3. **Post-visit** → Share Feedback / Talk to Agent / View Listings (not more-info loop).
4. **Filter tap** → localized reply + localized filter buttons.
5. **Sold unit by name** → sold message + project listings button.

## Definition of done

- `buyerEnterpriseUx.service.test.ts` matrix passes
- `buyerCopyCompliance.test.ts` passes
- `npm run smoke` passes
- Deploy + prod health check

